accd (0.2.15) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Weather: fix 0x37 + welcome wire order — rainLevel at slot [12]
    and cloudLevel at [11] per WeatherStatus::serialize write order,
    pinned by the JSON-helper field names (FUN_140114100).  Prior
    "clouds at [9], rain at [11]" reading made the cockpit render
    persistent rain while the external view correctly showed dry.
  * Welcome trailer: rewrite EventEntity body to match the real
    child serializers (CircuitEntity + GraphicsRules + CarSet +
    RaceEntity + WeatherStatus + WeatherData, 150 B for empty/dry)
    per FUN_1401185b0 readFromPacket anchors.
  * Lobby: 0xf2 keepalive body carries dynamic bytes (rain-derived
    load, weekend-time-derived sequence) per FUN_140048660 case 6.
    Hard-coded 0/0/0x0d body was getting the server delisted by the
    kson backend a few minutes after drivers>0 as "frozen".
  * Penalty system: match FUN_140125f50 behaviour for escalation.
    Added per-car per-exe-kind PenaltySheetState with counter +
    severity; ladder steps DT → SG30 → (force only) DQ on repeat
    admin issuance, per the bVar6=(force+2)*2 rule in the decomp.
  * Auto-penalties: server-side 3-cut drive-through in
    h_out_of_track (mirrors ACC client's self-issued DT), 80 km/h
    pit-lane speeding DQ with the 22.22 m/s threshold fixed from
    22.5, and failed-to-serve auto-DQ (or SG30 when allowAutoDQ=0).
    All three fire a 0x2b chat broadcast with a reason suffix
    ("- cutting", "- pit speeding", etc.).
  * 0x3e results: +0x74 penalty_ms now sums TP5/TP15/unserved-DT
    (previously wrote 0), so race total reflects time penalties.
  * 0x36 leaderboard: emit ServerMonitorPenaltyShortcut values
    (0..35) instead of internal PEN_* so the client sees the
    correct penalty semantic (DriveThrough_Cutting vs
    DriveThrough_RaceControl, etc.).
  * Session bests: DQ'd and unused cars no longer contribute to
    the session-best lap / sector displayed on the leaderboard
    sidebar.
  * 0x41 ACP_REPORT_PENALTY body reader fixed to u8+u8+u64+i32
    (was i32+f32+i32); still informational-only since client ptype
    is ServerMonitorPenaltyShortcut, not exe param_5.

 -- Renaud Allard <renaud@allard.it>  Fri, 17 Apr 2026 18:55:00 +0200

accd (0.2.14) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Lobby: report OVERTIME as phase=5 (kson backend silently delists
    servers that emit phase 6 or 7).
  * Lobby: collapse COMPLETED and ADVANCE to WAITING for the same
    reason — keeps the server visible through transient end-states.
  * Race sector splits: stop dropping the first 0x20 per car.  The
    drop kept lap_count one lap behind the client, so race lap-0
    appeared to start after the S/F line instead of at it.  Kunos
    counts the formation lap as lap 1 with IsOutLap set; the
    existing car_field bit 2 check already excludes it from
    best_lap.
  * Welcome trailer: rewrite the WeatherData block to match
    FUN_14011e660 (12 × u32 + two variable u32 lists).  The previous
    ad-hoc layout injected non-zero constants into slots the client
    reads as authoritative cockpit weather hints, producing
    persistent rain on the windshield while 0x37 correctly reported
    dry outside.

